*Cypress weekly update*

Last week was a short week, but the tests seemed a little less flaky!

Failing tests:
• :white_check_mark:  `aihub-custom-function-field` race condition fixed
• :loading: `aihub-derived-field` , `view-home-page` and `ground-truth-info` I’m looking into
• :grey_question: `file-list`  can’t find selector “[data-testgroup^=REVIEW_LIST_FILE_CONTAINER]“, @Udit
• :grey_question: `search-app` the model response for “What is the revenue of Apple in 2023” changed somehow, @Subash
Skipped tests:
• hopefully `ground-truth-info` can be unskipped after I take a look at it
I'll look into file-list today. I made a big change to that component last week but the test was passing after I made test changes in the same PR?
@danny.lan btw did you make any changes to `ground-truth-info` already?
i’d like to get it working before i make more changes to solution accuracy that would break the current test
I haven’t made changes yet, although the most common error for the test is a timeout issue with `ensureBuildProjectExists` . I’m not sure why other tests aren’t failing because of this though
